    "instructions": [
        "Dice chicken into small pieces. Drizzle with olive oil and season generously with salt and pepper.",
        "In a large skillet over medium heat, sauté chicken in batches until browned. Set aside.",
        "Dice onion and add to the skillet. Deglaze with a bit of water if needed and sauté for 2-3 minutes until soft.",
        "Add diced tomatoes, tomato paste, pumpkin puree, coconut milk, and lemon juice. Mix well.",
        "Stir in brown sugar and all spices. Mix cooked chicken back into the pan.",
        "Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer for 10-15 minutes.",
        "Serve over rice and top with fresh cilantro and red pepper flakes if desired."
